   <template id="offer_letter">
	   <t t-call="fms_hrms.external_layout_inherit">
		   <t t-foreach="docs" t-as="doc">
			<div class="page">
				<div class="container">
				<style>
					hr {
						margin-top:0px;
						margin-bottom:0px;
						}
				</style>
				<h4 style="text-decoration: underline; text-align:center;"><b>OFFER LETTER</b></h4>
				<table>     
					<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
					<tr>
						<td width="20%"><b>Date</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;"><b>:</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"><b><span t-esc="doc.joining_date" /></b></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
					<tr>
						<td width="20%"><b>Name</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;"><b>:</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"><b><span t-esc="doc.name" /></b></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
					<tr>
						<td width="20%"><b>Nationality</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;"><b>:</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"><b><span t-esc="doc.country_id.name" /></b></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
					<tr>
						<td width="20%"><b>Passport No.</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;"><b>:</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"><b><span t-esc="doc.passport_id" /></b></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
					<tr>
						<td width="20%"><b>Address</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;"><b>:</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"><b><span t-esc="doc.street" />,<span t-esc="doc.street2" />,<span t-esc="doc.city" />,<span t-esc="doc.state_id.name" />,<span t-esc="doc.country_id.name" /></b></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
					<tr>
						<td width="20%"><b>Email Address</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;"><b>:</b></td>
						<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"><b><span t-esc="doc.work_email" /></b></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
						<td width="20%"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
                    </table>
                    <table>
						<p align="justify">
							Dear <span t-esc="doc.name"/>,
						</p>
						<p align="justify">
							We are pleased to offer you the position of <b><span t-esc="doc.job_id.name" /></b> with Global FMS
							Technology – Muscat, Oman subject to your Work Permit and Residence Visa being issued by the
							competent local authorities in the Sultanate of Oman.							
						</p>
						<p align="justify">
							This Letter is issued on the understanding that all the information given by you or data provided
							prior to and/or at the time of joining are true and entirely accurate. If it is found at any time that the
							information given by you is/are not correct or true and/or you have concealed any information, the
							Employer will have the right to terminate your appointment any time without any notice or
							compensation.
						</p>
					</table>
					<table>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="5%">I.</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Date of Joining</td>
							<td width="10%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"><span t-esc="doc.joining_date" /></td>
							<td width="20%"></td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">II.</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Designation</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"><span t-esc="doc.job_id.name" /></td>
							<td width="20%"></td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">III.</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Monthly Salary</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"></td>
							<td width="20%"></td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%"></td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Basic Salary</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"></td>
							<td width="20%"></td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%"></td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Accommodation</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"></td>
							<td width="20%"></td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%"></td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Transportation/Fuel</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"></td>
							<td width="20%"></td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%"></td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Mobile Allowance</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left;"></td>
							<td width="20%"></td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">IV.</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Additional Benefits</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							<td width="50%" style="text-align:left;">
							-Medical insurance for you and your family up to 4 persons<br/>
							-Your own residence visa<br/>
							-21 working days leave per year<br/>
							-1 x round trip ticket economy class to your home country (can be
							converted to cash) per year<br/>
							-You will be provided a car for your own transport requirements
							and company use and product testing<br/>
							</td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>                            
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">V.</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</td>
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:center;">:</td>
							
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
					</table>
					<table>
					<tr>
						<td width="10%"></td>            
						<td width="90%" style="text-align:justify;">In summary your role will be back office support for the following:<br/>
							1. All existing FMS TECH. products and solutions; including compliance with client’s
							requirements, regulations and technical requirements.<br/>
							2. Responsible for all new innovations and customer and project requirements; ie., compliance
							with standards, implementation, system settings and configurations and back office
							support..etc. and drive pilot projects to success; including driver fatigue, multiple speed
							limiter, eagle eye, and others. We are planning on having our own Driver Fatigue solution,
							which you will be involved in putting the core requirements and work closely with R&amp;D until
							it becomes a product. In addition, the Multiple Speed Limiter is a new technology that we
							have make sure that it works and works well as it may become mandatory on 10,000
							vehicles by next year.. we are 1 of 3 approved vendors so far.<br/>
							3. Training to our existing Technical Engineers and Technicians as well as existing clients.<br/>
							4. Interface and support with FMS TECH R&amp;D and support team.<br/>
							5. Quality assurance of existing and new products and working remotely with the R&amp;D team
							on new upgrades, versions, and new products<br/>
							6. Provide Technical support.<br/>
							7. Business Analyst<br/>
							8. Pre-sales technical support and competency.<br/>
							9. Working remotely with R&amp;D team on all new integrations, new product development, ..etc.,
							for local and regional opportunities.
						</td>
						</tr>
					</table>
					<table>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">VI.</td>            
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Probation Period</td>
							<td width="10%">:</td>
							<td width="60%">Subject to an initial probation period of three months (3)
											months during which your services may be terminated
											without notice or severance pay, termination of employment
											by either party shall be on one (1) month's notice in writing
											or payment of one (1) month’s salary in lieu of notice. Unused
											leave may not offset such notice<br/><br/>
											If your actions at any time constitute a serious breach of Employer’s
											standards of behaviour, the Employer may terminate your employment
											immediately, without notice.
							</td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">VII.</td>            
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Period of Contract</td>
							<td width="10%">:</td>
							<td width="60%">Two (2) years starting from date of joining. In case you decide
											to terminate the contract before completing the 2 years as per
											agreement, you need to pay Global FMS Technology the full cost
											of all expenses paid for your work permit and all work related
											expenses, including all costs paid by the company for any
											specialized trainings/certifications in any location, for company work.
							</td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">IX.</td>            
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Non-Disclosure Agreement</td>
							<td width="10%">:</td>
							<td width="60%">Your employment with Global FMS Technology creates a
											relationship of confidence and trust between you and the
											company with respect to certain information which may be
											confidential, proprietary or trade secrets. You shall not, at any
											time, whether during the subsistence of the Contract of
											Employment or after its expiry/termination, disclose the
											Information of the company which is confidential and
											proprietary to any third party, except for the fulfilment of your
											obligations as an employee of Global FMS Technology.<br/><br/>
											All materials produced are company sole legal property during
											the employment period and afterward, any leak or misuse of
											information is subject legal courts. You are required to sign the
											“Non-Disclosure Agreement” and strictly abide by its terms and
											conditions.
							</td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">X.</td>            
							<td width="20%" style="text-align:left; text-decoration: underline;">Terms and Conditions:</td>
							<td width="10%">:</td>
							<td width="60%">1. Evaluation and appraisal after 2 years may result in your salary
											increase based on management evaluation and company financial
											status.<br/><br/>
											2. Two months notice in writing will be required by either side to
											terminate the employment. In case of early termination of your
											employment contract, you will be paid salary only up to the actual
											days you have worked.<br/><br/>
											3. Office working hours 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM Sunday to Thursday. I expect
											you to work outside working hours or on Saturdays when needed.<br/><br/>
											4. This offer is subject to your declaration that you are suitably qualified,
											medically fit and experienced to perform the duties as per the job
											description in a competent manner.<br/><br/>
											5.The Company will not hold any responsibility if in case work
											permit cannot be issued due to any existing violation status with the
											local authorities in the Sultanate of Oman,; all charges, fees, and
											penalties shall be charged to your account.<br/><br/>
											6. Please read this Letter carefully before you agree to its terms
											by signing it on all pages, including the Appendix A, and the
											place marked below.<br/><br/>
											7. You are expected to join Employer and commence work on 15
											September 2018, upon fulfilling all the Joining Formalities as
											stipulated under Appendix A.
							</td>
						</tr>
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
						<tr><td><br></br></td></tr>              
					</table>
					<p style="text-align:left;"><b>For &amp; on Behalf of Global FMS Technology:</b></p>
					<p><br/></p>
